Benefits of central ECMO in children with sepsis

Larger cannula more blood flow

Survival rates increased from 50% to 80%

Pressure, Flow & Vascular Resistance

MAP: 100 mmHg

CVP: 5 mmHg

PAP: 15 mmHg

PVP: 10 mmHg

CO: 5 L/min

CO: 5 L/min

Ohms Law (electrical theory): Voltage = Current x Resistance

Hydraulic Equivalent: Pressure Drop = Mean Flow x Resistance

SVR = (MAP - CVP) / CO

PVR = (PAP - PVP) / CO

(Mean Arterial Pressure)

(Cardiac Output)

(Central Venous Pressure)

(Mean Pulmonary Arterial Pressure)

(Pulmonary Venous Pressure)

cvbmcri.com

Pressure, Flow & Vascular Resistance

MAP: 100 mmHg

CVP: 5 mmHg

PAP: 15 mmHg

PVP: 10 mmHg

CO: 5 L/min

CO: 5 L/min

SVR = (MAP - CVP) / CO

= (100 mmHg - 5 mmHg) / 5 L/min

= 19 mmHg.min/L

= 1.14 mmHg.s/mL

cvbmcri.com

Pressure, Flow & Vascular Resistance

MAP: 100 mmHg

CVP: 5 mmHg

PAP: 15 mmHg

PVP: 10 mmHg

CO: 5 L/min

CO: 5 L/min

PVR = (PAP - PVP) / CO

= (15 mmHg - 10 mmHg) / 5 L/min

= 1 mmHg.min/L

= 0.06 mmHg.s/mL
